sentences: Sanja Maletić (Serbian Cyrillic: Сања Малетић; born 27 April 1973) is a Bosnian-born Serbian pop-folk singer.
Sanja began her music career in the end of 1998.
She said of herself "I am a real Bosnian, loving strong and high-calorie food" and that her vice is "cigarettes and a good book"; her favourite book being Meša Selimović's Death and the Dervish.
